metadata.name: Pixel Tunnel II #491
metadata.description:
This is based on a technique I've used to create textured abstract art by starting with a base design and applying millions of small mutations. Each design has a minimum of 1,500,000 mutations.

This design is built in 2 phases.
Phase 1: Aggressive twisted pixel tunnels create a tangled root system.
Phase 2: Less aggressive straight lines break up the sharp root systems and make the colors blend together.

- Higher themes are more rare (50 max)
- Higher patterns are more rare (15 max)

metadata.name: Glomularus #189
metadata.description:
Glomularus is an exploration in generative, artificial life forms. The project is an extension of my Protobyte series, begun in 2004.

Driven by Verlet icosahedra and responsive tendrils, Glomulari live in a spherical virtual ecosystem (V-eco) enhanced through user interaction.

Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
  drag -> camera rotation
  drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
  scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
  1-9: add acceleration
  -, +: reduce | increase V-eco sphere radius
  f, g: reduce | increase fog
  p: screen capture

Tip:
To decrease creature acceleration, reduce V-eco sphere radius

Note:
Please post your favorite Glomularus screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

metadata.name: Perpetual Oscillations  #63
metadata.description:
Planes expand and contract over time in different rhythms. 

Display notes:
The work is intended to be viewed running live in the browser, and there is no set aspect ratio. The viewer is invited to explore the space and choose their viewpoint. 

Controls:
Left-clicking and dragging - rotate around the center 
right-clicking and dragging - pan around the space 
Scrolling - zoom in and out 
Press b - b-side 
Press o - go back to the origin 
Press 1 to 3 - change the pixel density
Adjusting pixel density or changing the screen size will bring you back to the origin. 

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Reading a book #552
metadata.description:
The formal structure of a book is beautiful by itself, but its aesthetic is the tacit atmosphere within which events take place in a story.

The WebGL real-time animation sets up an initial grid based on the fxhash. The grid cells get subdivided into another grid and the resulting cells become filled with pixels in color (~33%) or black and white (~66%).
The colored pixels come in 3 different coloring styles.
- Big Palette (~49%)
- Small Palette (~49%)
- Monochrome [b/w] (~2%)
4 noise algorithms modify the pixels of selected grid cells while at the same time 4 reset algorithms reassemble the initial image. The selected cells switch over time.

metadata.name: Mind Mess #9
metadata.description:
"This is the mess inside my mind!"

A mess of colorful shards spinning and moving by Voronoi effect. Each Voronoi cell - also called Thiessen Polygons - can be interpreted as a thought. As you can see, thoughts are always changing and never stay the same. Judgments, opinions, certainties, preferences...

metadata.name: Griddy #99
metadata.description:
《Griddy》started from a survey of Mondrian’s and Raven Kwok’s work. During the process, several primitive elements are put together to form 《Griddy》.

The palette is chosen from RYB, RGB, CMYK. Three possible thicknesses are chosen for the grid line, and with a possibility of the same color with the background, forming a “negative space” effect. Three ratios for the partition of space, and with a possibility of “inverted ratio” when dividing space. For filling the grid, three prime numbers will be randomly selected for each color. And finally, a possibility that the whole grid moves.

Coding with the lovely Pts.js.
